SIMPLE: axle_guard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Axle guard
<hw>Ax"le guard`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>The part of the framing of a
railway car or truck, by which an axle box is held laterally, and in
which it may move vertically; -- also called a <xex>jaw</xex> in the
United States, and a <xex>housing</xex> in England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Axletree</ent>⟦br⟧
